Make the source-built OTP target (`otp-<name>`) publicly visible.

discord/rules_elixir's elixir_build references the OTP install cross-repo as
`@erlang_config//<name>:otp-<name>`, but discord/rules_erlang @ b4b0191 generates that
`erlang_build` target with no `visibility`, so it defaults to private and the Elixir build
fails analysis with a visibility error. The toolchains are already public; the raw OTP
target must be too. One-line, B3 "patch in place" — the exact integration gap between the
two pinned discord forks.

--- a/repositories/BUILD_internal.tpl
+++ b/repositories/BUILD_internal.tpl
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
     extra_configure_opts = %{EXTRA_CONFIGURE_OPTS},
     post_configure_cmds = %{POST_CONFIGURE_CMDS},
     extra_make_opts = %{EXTRA_MAKE_OPTS},
+    visibility = ["//visibility:public"],
 )

 erlang_toolchain(
